oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Construction of dormitory complex
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This photograph shows the construction of the dormitory complex next to the current James E. Walker Library. The buildings are named: Wood Hall, Felder Hall, Gore Hall, and Clement Hall. Wood and Felder were built in 1964, and Gore and Clement (in construction in the photo) were built in 1965. Architect, Wheeler. Contractor, Melson.
